@node Top-Level Files
@appendixsec Top-Level Files

@table @file
@item Makefile
Root build graph for the kernel, packaged userspace, disk and ISO images, QEMU
launch, and documentation generation.

@item README.md
Short human-readable overview of the project.

@item .gitignore
Repository ignore rules, including generated build and documentation outputs.
@end table

@node Kernel Boot Files
@appendixsec Kernel Boot Files

@table @file
@item kernel/linker.ld
Kernel linker script.

@item kernel/boot/boot.asm
Multiboot2 header, early paging setup, long-mode transition, and handoff to
@code{kernel_main}.

@item kernel/boot/interrupts.asm
Assembly helpers for loading the GDT and IDT, syscall entry, user-mode entry
and exit, and exception stubs.
@end table

@node Kernel Header Files
@appendixsec Kernel Header Files

@table @file
@item kernel/include/common.h
Small shared macros and reboot command constants.

@item kernel/include/console.h
Console API and framebuffer information structure.

@item kernel/include/console_font.h
Built-in console font dimensions and glyph table declaration.

@item kernel/include/ext2.h
Public interface of the ext2/ext3 backend.  The file keeps its historical name
even though the implementation now supports both formats.

@item kernel/include/fs.h
VFS-level path, mode, backend, and lookup interfaces.

@item kernel/include/gdt.h
GDT and TSS loader interface.

@item kernel/include/idt.h
IDT initialization interface.

@item kernel/include/initramfs.h
Initramfs entry representation and lookup interface.

@item kernel/include/input.h
Combined serial and keyboard input interface.

@item kernel/include/io.h
Inline x86 port-I/O, MSR, control-register, TSC, and FS-base helpers.

@item kernel/include/keyboard.h
Keyboard polling interface and combo-signal enumeration.

@item kernel/include/kmalloc.h
Kernel heap allocator interface.

@item kernel/include/multiboot2.h
Multiboot2 tag structures and lookup helpers used by the kernel.

@item kernel/include/power.h
ACPI and machine power-control interface.

@item kernel/include/process.h
Process table types, wait-state metadata, signal handler metadata, and process
management interfaces.

@item kernel/include/serial.h
Serial console interface.

@item kernel/include/string.h
Kernel-private memory and string routines.

@item kernel/include/syscall.h
Saved syscall-frame layout and syscall entry API.

@item kernel/include/userland.h
Bootstrap userland loader interface.

@item kernel/include/vm.h
User VM layout constants and VM-space interfaces.
@end table

@node Kernel Source Files
@appendixsec Kernel Source Files

@table @file
@item kernel/src/main.c
Top-level kernel startup and shell-launch policy.

@item kernel/src/multiboot2.c
Multiboot2 tag scanning helpers for modules, ACPI tables, and framebuffer
information.

@item kernel/src/console.c
Main console implementation, ANSI handling, framebuffer rendering, and text-cell
model.

@item kernel/src/console_font.c
Built-in 8x16 bitmap font table.

@item kernel/src/serial.c
COM1 initialization and polled serial I/O.

@item kernel/src/input.c
Input multiplexer over serial and keyboard.

@item kernel/src/keyboard.c
Polled PS/2 keyboard scancode translator.

@item kernel/src/power.c
ACPI parsing and machine halt, reboot, and shutdown logic.

@item kernel/src/gdt.c
Runtime GDT, TSS, and kernel-stack setup.

@item kernel/src/idt.c
IDT construction and vector installation.

@item kernel/src/exceptions.c
Exception report printer.

@item kernel/src/kmalloc.c
Kernel heap allocator.

@item kernel/src/vm.c
Kernel and per-process page-table management.

@item kernel/src/initramfs.c
Read-only initramfs parser and entry indexer.

@item kernel/src/ext2.c
Ext2/ext3 filesystem implementation used for the @file{/usr} mount.  The file
keeps its historical name even though the implementation now supports both
formats.

@item kernel/src/fs.c
VFS dispatcher over initramfs and the ext2/ext3 backend.

@item kernel/src/process.c
Process table allocator, lookup, and pending-signal bookkeeping.

@item kernel/src/userland.c
Bootstrap ELF loader and initial shell launcher.

@item kernel/src/syscall.c
The main syscall subsystem: descriptor model, path resolution, pipes, waiting,
signals, scheduling, exec, fork-like calls, and syscall dispatch.

@item kernel/src/string.c
Kernel-local @code{memcpy}, @code{memmove}, @code{strlen}, and related helper
implementations.
@end table

